<def f='linux-4.14.y/fs/ext4/resize.c' l='1572' ll='1637' type='int ext4_group_add(struct super_block * sb, struct ext4_new_group_data * input)'/>
<doc f='linux-4.14.y/fs/ext4/resize.c' l='1559'>/* Add group descriptor data to an existing or new group descriptor block.
 * Ensure we handle all possible error conditions _before_ we start modifying
 * the filesystem, because we cannot abort the transaction and not have it
 * write the data to disk.
 *
 * If we are on a GDT block boundary, we need to get the reserved GDT block.
 * Otherwise, we may need to add backup GDT blocks for a sparse group.
 *
 * We only need to hold the superblock lock while we are actually adding
 * in the new group&apos;s counts to the superblock.  Prior to that we have
 * not really &quot;added&quot; the group at all.  We re-check that we are still
 * adding in the last group in case things have changed since verifying.
 */</doc>
